COMMENT     Reprint for [2] and clean copy sequence for [12],[5] kindly
            provided by P.Collins, 21-FEB-1986.
            Respiratory syncytial virus is a negative-strand RNA pleomorphic
            enveloped virus of the genus Pneumovirus.  The matrix protein has
            no homology with the matrix proteins of other negative-stranded RNA
            viruses, implying that RS virus has undergone extensive
            evolutionary divergence.  Two unidentified reading frames which
            potentially encode proteins were located: one overlaps the matrix
            protein and the other the F protein.  The biological significance
            of these two reading frames is not clear.  The positive strand is
            shown.
